                                                </div>
                                            </a>
                                        </td></tr>
                                    
                                        
                                        <tr class="biblio-image-tile "><td class="col-sm-3">
                                            <a id="img-1532206-img131468" data-pos="" href="#modal-image" data-modal-toggle="true" class="biblio-image-tile-a ga-click-event apporder order title desc" data-imgid="1532206-img131468" data-lityx data-category="Extracted Images" data-label="biblio: image thumbnail" data-value="1532206-img131468" data-apporder="p. 19" data-order="2" data-imgid="1532206-img131468" data-imgsrc="/biblio/1532206/image/001/522/0015228/1/0131468.png" data-title="Figure 1" data-desc="&lt;em&gt;The Kratky plot of I*Q&lt;sup&gt;5/3&lt;/sup&gt; vs. Q for selected stars at four pH values for&lt;/em&gt; (a) DVB-PSPDMAEMA, (b) DVB-PS-PDMAEMA&lt;sub&gt;50%&lt;/sub&gt;/PEGMA&lt;sub&gt;50%&lt;/sub&gt; (c) DVB-PS-PMA&lt;sub&gt;50%&lt;/sub&gt;/PEGMA&lt;sub&gt;50%&lt;/sub&gt; (d) DVB-PSPEGMA (e) DVB-PS-PMAA. Data are shifted by a multiplication factor for clarity." data-ostiid="1532206">
                                                <div class="biblio-image-tile-inner">
                                                    <small class="name">Figure 1<small class="float-right text-muted" style="margin-right: .5em;top: 3px;position: relative;">(p. 19)</small><span class="d-none type">figure</span></small>
                                                    <img class="img-responsive mt-0-5" loading="lazy" alt="Figure 1" src="/biblio/1532206/image/001/522/0015228/1/t0131468.png"/>
                                                </div>
                                            </a>
                                        </td></tr>
                                    
                                        
                                        <tr class="biblio-image-tile "><td class="col-sm-3">
                                            <a id="img-1532206-img131469" data-pos="" href="#modal-image" data-modal-toggle="true" class="biblio-image-tile-a ga-click-event apporder order title desc" data-imgid="1532206-img131469" data-lityx data-category="Extracted Images" data-label="biblio: image thumbnail" data-value="1532206-img131469" data-apporder="p. 20" data-order="3" data-imgid="1532206-img131469" data-imgsrc="/biblio/1532206/image/001/522/0015228/1/0131469.png" data-title="Figure 2" data-desc="&lt;em&gt;Measured scattering curves for DVB-PS-PEGMA series in water from pH 9.48 (top) to pH 2.76&lt;/em&gt; (bottom). Experimental data are shown by colored dots and are shifted by a multiplication factor for clarity. Black solid lines are fits to the Dozier model, with the parameters given in Table S1. A metric of the experimental error is given by max(Err(Q)/I(Q)). The insert depicts the measured Guinier R&lt;sub&gt;G&lt;/sub&gt; for the 100% PEGMA series as a function of pH. The DVB-PS-PEGMA star polymer is composed of a crosslinked DVB core (orange), with diblock arm chemistries comprised of an inner hydrophobic pol-ystyrene block (black with y = 33), and outer hydrophilic PEGMA region (blue with x=30)." data-ostiid="1532206">
                                                <div class="biblio-image-tile-inner">
                                                    <small class="name">Figure 2<small class="float-right text-muted" style="margin-right: .5em;top: 3px;position: relative;">(p. 20)</small><span class="d-none type">figure</span></small>
                                                    <img class="img-responsive mt-0-5" loading="lazy" alt="Figure 2" src="/biblio/1532206/image/001/522/0015228/1/t0131469.png"/>
                                                </div>
                                            </a>
                                        </td></tr>
                                    
                                        
                                        <tr class="biblio-image-tile "><td class="col-sm-3">
                                            <a id="img-1532206-img131470" data-pos="" href="#modal-image" data-modal-toggle="true" class="biblio-image-tile-a ga-click-event apporder order title desc" data-imgid="1532206-img131470" data-lityx data-category="Extracted Images" data-label="biblio: image thumbnail" data-value="1532206-img131470" data-apporder="p. 21" data-order="4" data-imgid="1532206-img131470" data-imgsrc="/biblio/1532206/image/001/522/0015228/1/0131470.png" data-title="Figure 3" data-desc="&lt;em&gt;(a) Measured scattering curves for DVB-PS-PDMAEMA series in water from pH 9.26 (top) to pH 3.18 (bottom) and (b) corresponding titration curve for DVB-PS-PDMAEMA.&lt;/em&gt; Black solid lines are fits to Dozier or PCS model, with the parameters given in Table S2. The arrow indicates the transition from the Dozier to PCS model fit with increasing pH. The insert depicts the measured Guinier R&lt;sub&gt;G&lt;/sub&gt; for the 100% Basic series as a function of pH. The outer hydrophilic block is PDMAEMA (blue with x=30); see Figure 1 caption for other details." data-ostiid="1532206">
                                                <div class="biblio-image-tile-inner">
                                                    <small class="name">Figure 3<small class="float-right text-muted" style="margin-right: .5em;top: 3px;position: relative;">(p. 21)</small><span class="d-none type">figure</span></small>
