                                                </div>
                                            </a>
                                        </td></tr>
                                    
                                        
                                        <tr class="biblio-image-tile tr-striped"><td class="col-sm-3">
                                            <a id="img-1532206-img131522" data-pos="" href="#modal-image" data-modal-toggle="true" class="biblio-image-tile-a ga-click-event apporder order title desc" data-imgid="1532206-img131522" data-lityx data-category="Extracted Images" data-label="biblio: image thumbnail" data-value="1532206-img131522" data-apporder="p. 22" data-order="5" data-imgid="1532206-img131522" data-imgsrc="/biblio/1532206/image/001/522/0015228/1/0131522.png" data-title="Figure 4" data-desc="&lt;em&gt;(a) Measured scattering curves in water from pH 9.47 (top) to pH 2.80 (bottom) and (b) corresponding titration curve for DVB-PS-PDMAEMA50%/PEGMA50% series&lt;/em&gt;. Black solid lines are fits to Dozier or PCS model, with the parameters given in Table S3. The arrow indicates the transition from the Dozier to PCS model fit with increasing pH. The insert depicts the measured Guinier R&lt;sub&gt;G&lt;/sub&gt; for the 50% basic series as a function of pH. The outer block is a random copolymer with PDMAEMA50%/PEGMA50% region (blue with x=30); see Figure 1 caption for other details." data-ostiid="1532206">
                                                <div class="biblio-image-tile-inner">
